You're hitting two separate constraints that combine into horizontal overflow on very small devices:

1) **Grid-item intrinsic min‑width** — Grid children default to `min-width:auto`, so they won’t shrink below their contents. In your Contact section, each card is a grid child (`.contact-grid > *`). fileciteturn0file1  
2) **A child with its own minimum size** — the “Other” text box in the radio group has `min-width: min(320px, 60vw)` and the label is `inline-flex` (no wrapping inside the label), so at tiny widths the label’s row can become wider than its card. fileciteturn0file1

Below is a **surgical CSS patch** that eliminates the overflow without changing layout or JS:

---

## Drop‑in CSS patch

Append this near the end of `assets/css/corporate-1.9.7.css`:

```css
/* ================================
   CONTACT: XS overflow hardening
   ================================= */

/* Let grid children shrink with the viewport (safe globally) */
.contact-grid > * {
  min-width: 0; /* overrides grid default min-width:auto */
}

/* Inputs should never exceed their container */
.section--contact input[type="text"],
.section--contact input[type="email"],
.section--contact input[type="tel"],
.section--contact textarea {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 100%;
}

/* When space is tight, allow the "Other" text box to wrap under its label */
@media (max-width: 359.98px) {
  .option--other {
    flex-wrap: wrap;           /* allow children to break to a new line */
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 8px 10px;             /* slightly denser on XS */
  }
  .option--other input[type="text"] {
    /* override global min(320px,60vw) so it cannot force the card wider */
    min-width: 0;
    flex: 1 1 100%;
    width: 100%;
  }

  /* Slightly tighter card padding to reclaim a few px on ultra-narrow phones */
  .contact-card,
  .contact-form {
    padding: 12px;
  }
}

/* Optional: give the grid a touch more usable width on very small phones */
@media (max-width: 399.98px) {
  .contact-grid {
    max-width: 96vw; /* was 92vw; reduces side margins to cut risk of scrollbars */
  }
}
```

**Why this works**

- `min-width: 0` on `.contact-grid > *` removes the intrinsic floor that was preventing the left and right cards from shrinking with the viewport. (Your current grid uses `grid-template-columns: 1fr` under 1000px, so both cards are grid children.) fileciteturn0file1  
- The radio group’s “Other” field had a minimum inline size (`min-width: min(320px, 60vw)`) inside an `inline-flex` label, so it couldn’t break to the next line. Allowing **wrap on `.option--other`** and overriding the **min‑width on its text input** at ≤360px prevents that child from forcing the **right card** wider than the viewport. fileciteturn0file1  
- For extra headroom at 320–360px, trimming card padding a bit and (optionally) raising the container from **92vw → 96vw** reduces the chance of a horizontal scrollbar by a couple of character widths, without changing the design on normal phones. fileciteturn0file1

